data.title: OMG So good!!!
data.text:
My son suggested 5 Fusion for dinner.  I made a reservation for Saturday night.  

The restaurant was busy, we were seated soon after we arrived.  We ordered drinks and appetizers. 

We had the scallops and Korean beef ribs.  Both were delicious.  

For dinner we ordered the shrimp and lobster curry.  (We don't eat shrimp unless it is sustainable we asked to hold the shrimp and use more lobster.) We also ordered spicy salmon, spicy octopus, Steve McQueen roll and toro.  Everything was so good.  

5 Fusion has a great wine list and drink selection.  I love dessert wines and I am so happy when I find a place that has Sauternes.  

We had dessert, my favorite was the cardamom panna cotta.  

I cannot wait to return!   

The service was excellent.   We had a wonderful time.

data.title: Sophisticated, mind-blowing food
data.text: Five Fusion is an elevated dining experience with unique interpretations of Japanese-inspired dishes.

data.title: A really good sushi place!
data.text: We really enjoy sushi and Five Fusion rises above the other sushi places in Bend.  The wait staff was very knowledgeable about all the ingredients and preparation of each of their rolls.  They have an IPA roll that captures the essence of Bend with a beer infused salmon on it.  Great atmosphere and cozy.

data.title: If you love sushi, you'll love Five Fusion
data.text: Make a reservation as this is one place that will be full on a Friday or Saturday night. Good food choices and the wait staff is friendly and helpful

data.title: Fantastic.
data.text: Went in because I have heard so many good things about this place and Sushi is a favorite of mine. Angry Mango cocktail is amazing and the Steve McQueen Roll was everything I could have hoped for. Great setting cool atmosphere and service was top notch. Would definitely visit again.

data.title: Inventive food in trendy environment
data.text: I was a solo diner walk-in after a long meeting.  At 8 pm I was seated promptly but the dining floor was very busy - many tourists.  My waitress (whose name I failed to get but would give her a shout out here if I had) was helpful in guiding my drink and dining decisions - just the right mix of "there" when you want her to be, and "not there" when you don't want to be asked more questions. The sake list is limited but good. I wish I'd had other diners at the table - I wanted to try all the sushi rolls! Had a lovely housemade ice cream trio for dessert.  This is sure a sign that Bend is not the dusty old town it used to be -- 5 Fusion is one indication Bend is one trendy place.

data.title: Delicious creative Asian food and drinks
data.text: Everything we had here was delicious, except the salad was a bit underdressed.  The sesame chicken and the seafood stuffed shiitakes were amazing. Great service, too.

data.title: Loved this place
data.text:
Had a recommendation from friends , so went the first night there and enjoyed it so much we went back the last night.  Only 4 nights in Bend) This place had the best food.  Loved the avocado appetizer.  Sushi rolls good too. 2nd time I had the duo duck and friend had the shrimp curry, both fantastic.
The Banoffee dessert was in my top 5 of all time favorites.  This place needs a higher rating

data.title: Top class sushi
data.text: Incredible sushi with interesting innovative options as well as the classic favorites. We walked in without a reservation, just the two of us and were seated on the fun circular tables. We enjoyed choosing and picked some dishes we'd not even heard of before. The service was great, and it felt like a real treat dining here.

data.title: Super Expensive!
data.text: We sat outside on a nice evening and received excellent service.  The food was very good but very expensive.  I had the shrimp and lobster curry.  It didn't have any big pieces of lobster, and had three or four pieces of shrimp.  At $24, it seemed very costly compared to other places we've had a similar dish.  We also had two types of sushi:  a tuna flight and a California Roll for a total of $36!  Everything was tasty, but realistically, we've eaten at many Asian restaurants and these prices just seemed over the top.  And for that reason, we won't return.

data.title: Go for the sushi!
data.text: We started with the calamari, which was perfectly crispy but way too salty. Our Spicy Tuna and Rainbow Rolls were perfect and so fresh. The sushi we ordered just melted in our mouths. Beyond delicious! Service was impeccable, but the bartender was backed up. Loved the ambiance and decor.

data.title: Expensive but worth it
data.text: Oh my God... What a feast. Had so many amazing things such as seared scallops with bacon and edamame purée, Peking duck in steamed buns, pork gyoza, golden beets with candied nuts mixed with arugula and goat cheese, spider roll and cherry blossom roll (that had an awesome blend of fish and kiwi) and list goes on.  Hefty bill of $92 before tip for only two people but delicious nonetheless.

data.title: Delicious! Worth it! For special event or anytime!
data.text:
Oh my goodness...
We went for our anniversary, and made a reservation, which we recommend.

It was lovely!!! Food, service, location...

Meal of the night?
Fresh Lobster served 2 ways,
Lobster Sashimi w. Yuzu sauce and Lobster claw-meat tempura.
OH MY!!
And they do Gluten-Free (GF) really well!

We, also, ordered the Steve McQueen Roll as GF and it was great.

Dessert is not to be missed...they have a great pastry chef!

Seriously...Enjoy!

data.title: Much more than sushi
data.text: We almost didn't go here because we weren't looking for a sushi bar, but the other (cooked) food is spectacular and imaginative.  The setting is also lovely, with a high ceiling soothing decoration.

data.title: Love sushi
data.text: I am a huge fan of sushi. It's fresh the service is amazing the food comes almost right after u order.  Need to make a reservation a head of time they book up fast. !!!!!!

data.title: Can't talk, enjoying everything
data.text:
My friends took me here while I was visiting and the restaurant (and the company) did not disappoint.
We did the tasting menu and everything, and I mean everything was delicious! I travel a lot for my job and this restaurant was like dining in a fantastic 5 star restaurant in NYC. the presentation was beautiful, and the food is so memorable. I can't wait to visit my friends again so we can go back.
Tip - order the infused sake. you won't be disappointed!

data.title: Great Sushi
data.text: We had dinner there Saturday night with friends that live in Sisters.  They had been there before but it was our first time.  The sushi was fabulous.  Very fresh and some very inventive rolls.  Loved the atmosphere.  The cocktails were great too!

data.title: wish they had uni and better service
data.text: I know people like happy hour there, but the last time we went we wanted dinner--to spend money on real food, real sushi and drinks, and they stuck us at the worst table in the place against the front of the stairs even though there was nobody else around. We easily spent 3x as much as everyone else around us who was getting fried appetizers and cheap drinks. They never have uni. My friend ordered a roll, and the server suggested some sort of "house specialty" that just reeked of red onion. It's a neat spot, but just not worth being treated like a cheapskate when you clearly aren't and sushi is really not at the center of what they are doing. Rename is Five Fusion and Red Onion Bar.

data.title: The Perfect GALentines
data.text:
I made reservations here for Valentines Day weekend for my friend and I weeks in advance just to make sure we were able to get a reservation.
Everything from the ambiance, to the food and the service was perfect! They had "LOVE" specials for the evening and we basically wanted to order one of everything!

The only downside was that we were so full from dinner that we were unable to try out their amazing desserts! :(
Of all the Sushi Bars in Bend, this one is the absolute best! I would recommend to everyone! While it is a little expensive, it's totally worth it! Especially for a special event or occasion! We will definitely be back!

data.title: YUMM!!!
data.text: Always great.  They have fresh yummy sushi, spicy edamame, and the short rib are delicious too.   We had a large group here and the service on drinks and ordering was a bit slow, but once the food started coming out it was great!  I highly recommend some of the specialty rolls, Steve McQueen,  and the one with the jalapeno slice on top are both AMAZING!!   Enjoy!
